<ol>
  <li>decision theory model for inference adds another ingredient to the sampling
model-<strong>the loss function</strong></li>
</ol>

<h4 id="framework-of-decision-theory">Framework of Decision Theory</h4>
<ol>
  <li>a set of possible of actions or decisions that the statistician could take
after abserving the data s.
    <ul>
      <li>here, the term actions and decisions have the same meaning</li>
      <li>the set of possible actions is denoted by <strong>A</strong>, and is called <strong>action space</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>To connect this actions with the statistical model, there is <strong>correct action
function</strong> \(A: \Omega \rightarrow A\)</li>
</ol>

